  "text": "In this paper, we use traces from Yahoo! production workloads to test the effectiveness of different models. The traces come from five Yahoo! data centers, which are located at Dallas (DAX), Washington DC (DCP), Palo Alto (PAO), Hong Kong (HK) and the United Kingdom (UK). Most of the core services, such as Web, Email, Messenger, etc., are provided in DAX, DCP and PAO. Chen et al. [CITATION_1] divided the traffic into two categories: 1) D2C, that the traffic between servers and clients, 2) D2D, that the traffic between different Yahoo! servers at different locations.",
